    "created_at": "2016-05-25T03:47:14Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-05-25T03:47:14Z",
    "body": "That makes sense actually, I was just expecting different behavior when Electron is spawned. Maybe an environment variable then? Which makes it not open a GUI dialog with the error, but instead logs it to stdout and then exits with the correct exit code. There are many use cases for spawning Electron, from headless testing, to my use-case of testing an Electron module I'm working on.\n"
